               <p>RICHARD WATERS. On the 5th of November I was walking up <placeName id="t18271206-173-crimeloc914">Ayre-street-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-173-crimeloc914" type="placeName" value="Ayre-street-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-173-crimeloc914" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-173-off912 t18271206-173-crimeloc914"></join>, about two minutes past six o'clock in the evening; I lost my handkerchief from my right hand coat pocket; I felt a slight pressure upon me, and I missed my handkerchief; I turned sharply round, and saw three men - the prisoner was one, and he ran away - I followed, and called Stop thief! he turned a corner, and threw my handkerchief down, and was stopped by an officer; I picked my handkerchief up; I am certain of his person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271206-173-person956">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COLTON
               <interp inst="t18271206-173-person956" type="surname" value="COLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271206-173-person956" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271206-173-person956" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the cry of Stop thief! the prisoner was the first person running, and I stopped him; Mr. Waters came up, and I took the prisoner in charge. I received this handkerchief from Waters.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I heard the cry Stop thief! and ran to see what was the matter.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18271206-173-verdict915" type="verdictDescription">
